1. The survival rate was higher for patients who had clinical remission after preoperative chemotherapy.
2. The median survival time (MST) for patients who had clinical remission after preoperative chemotherapy was 42.10 months.
3. The median survival time (MST) for patients who did not have clinical remission after preoperative chemotherapy was 35.33 months.
4. The difference in survival rates did not reach statistical significance.
5. The P-value for the difference in survival rates was 0.630.
